adviseScripts.text: Hey Commander, you've been spacing out
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: in the office for a while.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Are you bored or something?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Yes.
Nope.
I knew it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: My eyes never deceive me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: It's like you have "Help! I'm bored and I want to do something!" written all over your face.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: How about a strawberry candy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Oh, come on!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Even I can see that you have "I'm bored" written all over your face.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: But if you say you're not, I'll believe you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Have a strawberry candy, then?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Diesel while eating the strawberry candy she gives me.
Soline said she was tired of eating strawberry candy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: She said she wanted something else for a change.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What should I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: No more candy for her.
Give her some better strawberry candy.
Hm... Is that really the only way?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: It makes me feel so sad...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Whoa, fantastic idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I haven't gone shopping for candy in a long time. Strawberry candies, here I come!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel tells me all about her favorite strawberry candy.
Heeey... Commander,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Brid has been feeling down lately.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'm worried about her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What can I do to cheer her up?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Ask Soline to stay away from Brid for a while.
Help Brid with some of her work.
Haha! You mean, remove her main source of stress?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I wouldn't mind that. And then I could spend more time with Soline, too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text:
I can help Brid and play with Soline at the same time!
That's what I call a win-win scenario!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: That would make Brid even more upset!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: She's so responsible, she has to do all her work herself or she'll feel stressed out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Buuut... I guess I should go ask her if she needs help, just in case!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I chat with Diesel about ways to help Brid relax.
Commander, do you like soft flavors or strong flavors?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Soft.
Strong.
Oh. I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I had no idea! I always give you my strongest strawberry candy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I guess I should give you the strawberry milk candy instead.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Haha! Me, too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I like pure strawberry candy with no milk!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: From now on, I'll give you all my strongest, purest candy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I have a cheerful conversation with Diesel about strawberry candy preferences.
Ding dong! Out of the way!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: AZX is coming through! Ding dong!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: She's out of tune, but just let her sing.
She's out of tune, so tell her to stop.
Passengers over there! Please be careful!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: The train is coming through! Ding dong!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Thank you for letting me finish the song, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Oops! I was just so carried away by the music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Sooorry, Commander!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I have a cheerful chat with Diesel.
Commander, did you like Ark Rangers when you were a kid?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I was a huge fan.
I never got into them.
Haha, I see!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: You must have been so adorable!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I wish I could see photos of you when you were little.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Oh! You were one of those cool kids who didn't care about trends.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: You must have been so adorable!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Diesel about childhood.
Hm... What a pickle...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I really want to make the AZX more pretty.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What should I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Make it the same color as strawberry candy.
The AZX is already perfect. No need to decorate.
Oh! That would be so cute!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text:
Hm... But...
Its current appearance would be lost forever!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Oh, my! What a pickle...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: You're right. The AZX is already perfect
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: without any additional decoration.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I didn't even consider that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Thank you sooo much!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I talk with Diesel about the cute AZX.
What a beautiful day!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: If you could take a day off on a nice day like this,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: what would you do, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Sleep in the office.
Practice my singing.
Wow! You must be so tired all the time, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: But staying cooped up inside will only make you more tired in the end.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Taking a walk around the Outpost would be a better choice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Practice singing? That sounds so exciting!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Can I do it with you?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I chat with Diesel about how to have a pleasant holiday.
Hey! There's something I want to know.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What would I be doing if I hadn't come to work at Arc Express?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Probably a pop idol.
Definitely a kindergarten teacher.
Do you really think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Wow! Just thinking about it makes me so happy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I feel like my dream has come true!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Oh... Yes. I do love playing with kids.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I guess I would make a good teacher.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I spend some time chatting with Diesel.
Commander, if time machines were real,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: would you want to go back and change anything?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Yes.
No.
Gee! So, you feel the same as me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I didn't expect that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: But it makes sense. After all, everyone has regrets.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: That includes me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I also have a moment that I really, really regret.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Knowing that you feel the same makes me feel comforted.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, I knew it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I admire the way you live without regrets, Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I spend a quiet time with Diesel reminiscing about the past.
If you could get on the AZX right now and go anywhere you wanted,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: where would you go?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Somewhere with a lush forest and babbling brook.
Somewhere near the ocean where I could hear the sound of crashing waves.
So you prefer forested areas?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Glancing at the mountains and streams outside the window
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: while riding the AZX would be a real treat.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'm a big fan of the ocean as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Sitting by the ocean at night, dipping my toes in the sand, listening to the waves coming in and out...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I could do that forever.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Oh boy, this makes me want to hop in the AZX right now and set off!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I talk about the various places we want to visit.
I really like the color of the uniform I'm wearing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What's your favorite color, Commander?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Blue.
White.
Hey, me too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Nothing beats blue.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I see the color blue, it feels like my mind is clearer than before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I can feel my entire body become more at ease.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: White is a nice and clean color.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Very appropriate for you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I talk a little more about our favorite colors.
Every button has to be in place with our uniforms when we're on duty.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What type of clothing style do you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Cool and casual.
Prim and proper.
Really? I didn't expect you to be into a more laidback style.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I prefer it myself as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I wonder what you'd look like with a more casual look...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'm sure it'd look good on you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...I think you could rock a casual look too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I think you could pull off a more stylish look too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'm sure you'd cut quite the figure!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I spent some time talking about our favorite clothing styles.
Brid is always pounding down coffee while she's working... I'm actually a little worried.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything else I could get her to drink instead of coffee?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Make her a sweet strawberry latte.
Why change it? Nothing beats a good cup of joe while you're working.
Sounds delicious! My mouth's watering just thinking about it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'll go and buy all the ingredients.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Fresh strawberries may be tough to find though...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I hope Brid will like it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: But I want to make her something new...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I suppose you're right though. Coffee is second to none in terms of increasing your work efficiency.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I should buy her a top-of-the-line coffee grinder!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I try to figure out other drinks that Brid might enjoy.
Whenever I smell something nice, it puts me in a good mood.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What's your favorite smell?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Sweet fruits
Fresh flowers
Same! The fruits smell so nice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Especially strawberries!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Whenever I pick up the scent of strawberries, it's as if I'm having strawberry candy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Nothing puts me in a better mood!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: That's unexpected...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I thought you would like the smell of certain fruits better.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Anyway, I'll keep that in mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I talked more about our favorite scents.
I've heard certain animals dance after you give them a compliment.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: In your mind, what's the ultimate compliment?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Any compliment from you.
Any compliment is fine by me.
In that case,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'll be sure to compliment you every day!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I wonder if you'd start dancing if I gave you enough compliments, hehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: You seem like a really nice person.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'm happy to have you around.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I hope you can stick around for a long time!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel showered me with compliments for the rest of the day.
Instead of texting, I prefer calling people.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What do you prefer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Texting.
Phone calls.
In that case,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I'll text you more from here on out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: If you ask me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: talking with someone over the phone is the way to go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: You can more easily tell how the person is feeling when you can hear their voice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Next time I'm bored, I'll give you a call.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I had a nice heart-to-heart.
For me, it's the little things that bring me joy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What's something small that makes you happy?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I haven't really thought about it.
Talking with you.
Don't worry, I'm sure there's plenty out there
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: that would make you happy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: If anything comes to mind, be sure to let me know!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I didn't realize you enjoyed talking with me so much!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Talking with you makes me happy as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: We should try and talk a little more often.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I have a conversation about happiness.
It's always so hard picking out a birthday present.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Is there anything you would want as a birthday present?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Strawberry cake.
It's the thought that counts.
Oooh, sounds delicious!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Then again, anything with strawberries is bound to be good.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: All right then, I'll bake a strawberry cake for your birthday.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... kind of a cookie-cutter answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: You'll be one tough cookie to buy a birthday present for.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I talked more about birthday presents.
I watched a documentary yesterday, and it talked a lot about death.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: It got me thinking...
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: What age do you want to live until?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I want to be immortal.
I want my life to be short and sweet.
That'd be great!
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I want you to live a long long time as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Don't you think it's sad to live such a short life though?
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: I want you to live a long long time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Diesel

adviseScripts.text: Diesel and I talk about our times, and when they'll be up.
